  "title": "Regional Development Head",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p>The Regional Development head is responsible for overseeing business operations, sales performance, and team management across ASEAN region. The role ensures company objectives are met by driving revenue growth, maintaining operational excellence, and leading regional teams to achieve targets. We are an experienced company in electrical and cabling works. We want to expand into ASEAN as a building automation / process automation solution provider. We are looking for someone who has some business experience in IT, Networks and Automation solutioning. <br /><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>·        Lead and manage end-to-end regional operations across multiple locations</p><p>·        Develop and implement regional business, sales and growth strategies</p><p>·        Achieve assigned revenue, margin, and operational performance targets</p><p>·        Monitor regional KPIs, budgets, forecasts, and cost controls</p><p>·        Lead,coach, and performance-manage branch, area, and site managers</p><p>·        Ensure compliance with Singapore regulatory requirements, company policies, and SOPs</p><p>·        Build and maintain strong relationships with key clients, partners, and stakeholders</p><p>·        Analyze market trends, competition, and customer requirements to support decision-making</p><p>·        Drive operational efficiency, process improvements, and service quality standards</p><p>·        Handle escalations related to operations customers, and team performance</p><p>·        Collaborate with Head Office and cross-functional teams on strategy execution</p><p>·        Prepare and submit accurate management reports and performance reviews</p><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><p>·        Minimum10–15years of must experience</p><p>·        Proven experience in new market entry, business development, and order generation across Southeast Asia, particularly Malaysia, Thailand, and Indonesia, involving new ventures or regional expansion projects</p><p>·       The must possess strong expertise in developing and expanding automation solutions, supported by hands-on experience in networking and computer technologies, and be able to engage in technical-level discussions directly</p><p>·        Demonstrated capability to engage in detailed technical discussions with customers, partners,system integrator, and internal engineering teams</p><p>·        Expertisein developing, positioning, and expanding automation solutions portfolios across diverse industries and customer segments</p><p>·        Ability to translate technical requirements into commercial proposals, business cases,and scalable solutions</p><p>·        We looking direct to talk technical level Expertise in order</p><p>·        Strong understanding of regional customer needs, regulatory considerations, and market experience within Southeast Asia</p>",
